article.headline: Montana 78, Carroll (Mont.) 58
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Mathias Ward scored 26 points to lead Montana to a 78-58 victory over Carroll College (Mont.) on Saturday night. Montana (4-3) also got 15 points from Keron Deshields, including three 3-pointers, and 14 points and seven assists from Kareem Jamar. Montana had a solid night from the floor. It shot 48.4 percent, and connected on 8 of 18 3-point attempts. Nick Jones led Carroll (0-8) with 19 points and eight rebounds. He hit three 3-pointers. Dennis Mikelonis scored 14 points and Brett Ball scored 12. Montana shot 12 times from the foul line, making 10. Carroll only attempted nine from the line but made eight.
